<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1744,2010]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1744,1768]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[274,340,1744,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 5 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1640,1664]" captionTargetBox="[347,1239,208,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[341,1246,194,1594]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 5 – 7. Miroculis (M.) fazzariensis sp. nov. Male imago. 5. Dorsal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Lateral view of head and thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216070/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
Fig. 
<number box="[324,340,1744,1767]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Yellowish brown. Antennae: pedicel and scape brown; flagellum pale. Ocelli: white with dark brown base. Eyes: lower portion black;dorsal portion of eyes on short stalk (
<figureCitation box="[910,977,1779,1802]" captionStart="FIGURE 5 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1640,1664]" captionTargetBox="[347,1239,208,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[341,1246,194,1594]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 5 – 7. Miroculis (M.) fazzariensis sp. nov. Male imago. 5. Dorsal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Lateral view of head and thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216070/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
Fig. 
<number box="[962,977,1779,1802]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
), with 
<number box="[1055,1122,1779,1802]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
large–sized facets in longest row, light orangish brown; distance between upper portion of compound eyes equal to width of an upper portion (
<figureCitation box="[1357,1422,1813,1836]" captionStart="FIGURE 5 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1640,1664]" captionTargetBox="[347,1239,208,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[341,1246,194,1594]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 5 – 7. Miroculis (M.) fazzariensis sp. nov. Male imago. 5. Dorsal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Lateral view of head and thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216070/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
Fig. 
<number box="[1407,1422,1813,1836]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1744,2010]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,283,1848,1872]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[299,403,1848,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 5 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1640,1664]" captionTargetBox="[347,1239,208,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[341,1246,194,1594]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 5 – 7. Miroculis (M.) fazzariensis sp. nov. Male imago. 5. Dorsal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Lateral view of head and thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216070/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
Figs. 
<number box="[360,403,1848,1871]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pro, meso and metanotum chestnut. Pleura and sterna brown with margins dark brown. Wings (
<figureCitation box="[159,264,1883,1906]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[167,1435,271,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,229,1938]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 4. Miroculis (M.) fazzariensis sp. nov. Male imago. 1. Forewing; 2. Hind wing; 3. Genitalia (ventral view); 4. Detail of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216069/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">
Figs. 
<number box="[221,264,1883,1906]" pageId="2" pageNumber="497" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
</figureCitation>
): forewing: longitudinal and cross veins brown; membrane translucent washed with brown except for some cells on anterior and middle region; cross veins surrounded narrowly by brown pigmentation. 
<collectingCountry box="[1176,1229,1917,1940]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="497">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing: longitudinal and cross veins brown; membrane translucent washed with brown, an area near costal projection unpigmented. Legs: broken off and lost.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,310,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[326,431,152,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 5 – 7" captionStartId="2.[151,255,1640,1664]" captionTargetBox="[347,1239,208,1587]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[341,1246,194,1594]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 5 – 7. Miroculis (M.) fazzariensis sp. nov. Male imago. 5. Dorsal view; 6. Lateral view; 7. Lateral view of head and thorax." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216070/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Figs. 
<number box="[388,431,152,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
</figureCitation>
). General color: brown translucent. Tergum I washed with brown; terga II–III with a median brownish spot; terga IV–VIII with two posterior median brownish spots, more intense on tergum VIII; terga VIII–IX orangish brown. Sterna I–VII translucent brown, sterna VIII–IX brownish orange.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,255,279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[318,419,256,279]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 4" captionStartId="1.[151,255,1962,1986]" captionTargetBox="[167,1435,271,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1435,229,1938]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 4. Miroculis (M.) fazzariensis sp. nov. Male imago. 1. Forewing; 2. Hind wing; 3. Genitalia (ventral view); 4. Detail of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/216069/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
Figs. 
<number box="[379,419,256,279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
</figureCitation>
) Length of styliger plate 
<quantity box="[690,787,256,279]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="498" unit="mm" value="0.27">0.27 mm</quantity>
, brown yellowish. Forceps: light brown, with a blackish spot on the outer and inner sides near the apex of the first segment; spines present from the base to the middle of forceps segment I. Penes: brown; long and slender with membranous apex. Filaments: broken off and lost.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,1041]" box="[199,617,359,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,503,359,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="498">Female imago and nymph:</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
